§ Definition ⦉
¶ ⦊
  ‖ Suppose $A_1, …, A_n$ is a␣
    <a href='/sheets/lists.html'>
      ‖ list ⦉
    </a>
    ␣of␣
    <a href='/sheets/finite_sets.html'>
      ‖ finite sets ⦉
    </a>
    ␣and $p: ∏_{i = 1}^{n} A_i → [0,1]$ is a␣
    <a href='/sheets/probability_distributions.html'>
      ‖ distribution ⦉
    </a>
    ␣on the (finite)␣
    <a href='/sheets/direct_products.html'>
      ‖ product ⦉
    </a>
    ␣$∏_{i = 1}^n A_i$. ⦉
⦉

¶ ⦊
  ‖ For $i ≠ j ∈ \set{1, …, n}$, the ❬conditional distribution❭
    of $i$ on $j$ is the function $p_{i | j}: A_i × A_j → 𝗥$
    defined so that that $p_{i | j}(\cdot, b)$ is the
    conditional distribution induced by conditioning on $\Set{a ∈
    ∏_{i = 1}^{n} A_i }{a_j = b}$. ⦉
⦉

¶ ⦊
  ‖ For $i,j = 1, …, n$ and $i ≠ j$, $p_i$, $p_{ij}$ and
    $p_{i|j}$ satisify
    ◇ ⦊
      ‖ p_{i | j}(b, c)p_{j}(c) = p_{ij}(b, c) ⦉

      ‖ \quad ⦉

      ‖ \text{for all } b ∈ A_i, c ∈ A_j ⦉
    ⦉⦉
⦉

